name: VNErrorCode
desc: Constants that identify the errors that the framework generates.

items.name: case OK
items.desc: The operation finished without error.

items.name: case dataUnavailable
items.desc: The data isn’t available.

items.name: case internalError
items.desc: An internal error occurred within the framework.

items.name: case invalidArgument
items.desc: An app passed an invalid parameter to a request.

items.name: case invalidFormat
items.desc: The format of the image is invalid.

items.name: case invalidImage
items.desc: The image is invalid.

items.name: case invalidModel
items.desc: The Core ML model is incompatible with the request.

items.name: case invalidOperation
items.desc: An app requested an unsupported operation.

items.name: case invalidOption
items.desc: An app specified an invalid option on a request.

items.name: case ioError
items.desc: An I/O error for an image, image sequence, or Core ML model.

items.name: case missingOption
items.desc: A request is missing a required option.

items.name: case notImplemented
items.desc: The method isn’t implemented in the underlying model.

items.name: case operationFailed
items.desc: The requested operation failed.

items.name: case outOfBoundsError
items.desc: An app attempted to access data that’s out-of-bounds.

items.name: case outOfMemory
items.desc: The system doesn’t have enough memory to complete the request.

items.name: case requestCancelled
items.desc: An app canceled the request.

items.name: case timeStampNotFound
items.desc: The system can’t find a timestamp.

items.name: case unknownError
items.desc: An unidentified error occurred.

items.name: case unsupportedRevision
items.desc: An app specified an unsupported request revision.

items.name: case unsupportedRequest
items.desc: An app attempted an unsupported request.
